Citation.sTitle: Viscosities and Interfacial Properties of I-Methyl-3-butylimidazolium Hexafluorophosphate and 1-Isobutenyl-3-methylimidazolium Tetrafluoroborate Ionic Liquids
Citation.sAbstract: Room temperature ionic liquids (RTILs) are potential alternative solvents in chemical reaction or separation process.  The viscosity of RTIL, interfacial properties of air-RTIL, organic compounds-RTIL, and solid-RTIL are of  general importance. The viscosities of I-butyl-3-methylimidazolium hexafluorophosphate ([BMIM][PF6D and  l-isobutenyl-3-methylimidazolium tetrafluoroborate ([iBeMIM][BF4D ionic liquids (ILs) have been determined  from (288.15 to 313.15) K. The surface tension/contact angle on solids of [BMIM][PF6] and [iBeMIM][BF4] ILs  have been measured at 298.15 K. The liquid-liquid interfacial tension for [BMIM][PF6] with 21 organic compounds  have also been determined at 298.15 K. The relationship between the interfacial tensions and activity coefficients  at infinite dilution of solutes in IL is discussed.
